You can not use helper functions except [env()](https://laravel.com/docs/helpers#method-env) inside config files in Laravel because those files are loaded and cached **way before**  `AppServiceProvider`&#160;in the pipeline and therefor you get `null`

If you want to get something from the database by a simple global function call, make your own

For example

`app/Helpers.php`

```php
&lt;?php

// Name it however you want
function getMerchant()
{
  $zarinpal = PaymentConfig::where(&#39;slug&#39;, &#39;zarinpal&#39;)-&gt;first();
  return $zarinpal
}
```

Load it to the composer class-map via `composer.json`

```json
&quot;autoload&quot;: {
        &quot;psr-4&quot;: {
            &quot;App\\&quot;: &quot;app/&quot;
        },
        &quot;classmap&quot;: [
            &quot;database/seeds&quot;,
            &quot;database/factories&quot;
        ],
        &quot;files&quot;: [
            &quot;app/Helpers.php&quot;
        ]
    },
```

Now you can call `getMerchant()`&#160;anywhere in your code (except config) and get the record out of the database

---
Insert through the helper using dot notation

```php
config([&#39;app.zarinpal.merchant&#39; =&gt; $zarinpal-&gt;merchant ?? 0]);
```
And access it like so
```php
config(&#39;app.zarinpal.merchant&#39;);
```

Note that this is a bad design decision, you should make a global helper function instead because config files load before anything else

